title: BOYS SOCCER: Quincy blanks North Quincy, 3-0
text: Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 8:31 AM Updated at 8:46 AM QUINCY -- Sophomores Leandro Batista and Clayton Rodrigues and junior Benito Carvalho scored for Quincy in a 3-0 win over North Quincy on Saturday night at Veterans Memorial Stadium. Rodrigues and junior Ali Mokallad had assists for Quincy. "North Quincy-Quincy games are just always very difficult," said Quincy coach Mark Spendlove. "Whatever the separation in talent, it always evens out and itâ€™s always a difficult game. There are no easy games. It was a great team effort tonight ."
